==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Episcopate
<hw>E*pis"co*pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>episcopatus</ets>, fr. <ets>episcopus</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧piscopat</ets>. See <er>Bishop</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>A bishopric; the office and dignity of a bishop.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The collective body of bishops.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The time of a bishop's rule.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Episcopate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Episcopate
<hw>E*pis"co*pate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Episcopated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Episcopating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To act as a bishop;
to fill the office of a prelate.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Feeding the flock <qex>episcopating</qex>.</q>
